<sect2 id="script-fu-circuit">
  <title>Line Nova</title>

  <indexterm>
    <primary>Filters</primary>
    <secondary>Render</secondary>
    <tertiary>Line Nova</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Line Nova</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect3>
    <title>Overview</title>
    <figure>
      <title>Example of Line Nova</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="JPG"
            fileref="images/filters/examples/render-taj-line-nova.jpg"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Filter <quote>Line Nova</quote> applied</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      <guimenuitem>Line Nova</guimenuitem> command is a script which fills
      a layer with rays emanating outward from its center using the FG color.
      All lines radiates from the center of the layer.  Rendered lines are
      cropped to be fit inside of the image.
    </para>
    <para>
      If you need adjust the center of lines, create a transparent image in
      slightly larger size than the original, and apply this script on it,
      then add a copy of the layer to the original image, and move the layer
      to the appropriate position.
    </para>
  </sect3>

  <sect3>
    <title>Options</title>
    <figure>
      <title><quote>Line Nova</quote> filter options</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="PNG"
            fileref="images/filters/options-render-line-nova.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      1
    </para>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Number of lines</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            By using this slider you can set the number of lines between 40
            to 1000. The default is 200.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Sharpness (degrees)</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            0.0-10.0 1.0
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Offset radius</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            0-2000 100
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>Randomness</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            1-2000 30
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
